# Paeonia Innovation - Environment Variables

# ============================================
# BACKEND API CONFIGURATION
# ============================================

# Railway Backend API URL
# Set this in Netlify environment variables to connect to your Railway backend
# Example: https://ai-chat-production-abc123.up.railway.app
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT include trailing slash
#
# Backend provides:
# - AI Chatbot responses (POST /api/chat)
# - Lead capture & CRM integration (POST /api/lead-capture)
# - Health checks (GET /api/health, GET /api/status)
# - Automatic sync to Membrain CRM with lead source tracking
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================

# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Set REACT_APP_API_URL to http://localhost:8000 (if running backend locally)
# 3. Or leave unset to use mock responses for frontend development

# NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT:
# 1. Go to Netlify Dashboard → Your Site → Site settings → Environment variables
# 2. Add variable:
#    - Key: REACT_APP_API_URL
#    - Value: https://your-railway-app.up.railway.app (your actual Railway URL)
# 3. Trigger a new deploy for changes to take effect

# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================

# - All React environment variables MUST start with REACT_APP_
# - Changes to .env files require restarting the dev server (npm start)
# - Changes to Netlify env vars require redeploying the site
# - Never commit .env.local to git (it's in .gitignore)
